copy, to Nicholas Cooke, Sullivan, and Jonathan Trumbull, Sr., in Stephen Moylans writing, 12 Nov., <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>;

<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Letter Book Copy: letters copied into a bound letter-book ]">LB</abbr>, to Cooke and Trumbull, 12 Nov., <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>;

<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Letter Book Copy: letters copied into a bound letter-book ]">LB</abbr>, to William Palfrey, 12 Nov., <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>;

<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Handwritten copies in one of the bound volumes used by the team of clerks on GW's headquarters staff who worked from 1781-83 under the direction of Lt. Col. Richard Varick to record correspondence, orders, instructions, and related items from GWs Revolutionary War papers ]">Varick transcript</abbr>, to Cooke and Trumbull, 12 Nov., <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>;

<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Handwritten copies in one of the bound volumes used by the team of clerks on GW's headquarters staff who worked from 1781-83 under the direction of Lt. Col. Richard Varick to record correspondence, orders, instructions, and related items from GWs Revolutionary War papers ]">Varick transcript</abbr>, to Palfrey, 12 Nov., <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>;

<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Handwritten copies in one of the bound volumes used by the team of clerks on GW's headquarters staff who worked from 1781-83 under the direction of Lt. Col. Richard Varick to record correspondence, orders, instructions, and related items from GWs Revolutionary War papers ]">Varick transcript</abbr>, to Sullivan, 12 Nov., <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0280-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0280-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>Gen. William Howes three proclamations, all dated 28 Oct. 1775, are printed in the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">New-England Chronicle: or, the Essex Gazette</span> (Cambridge, Mass.), 2 Nov. 1775.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0280-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0280-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>The other copies, except those addressed to Palfrey, read Reign instead of Ministry.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0280-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0280-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>The place is left blank in the other copies, except the ones addressed to Palfrey, which also read Portsmouth.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0280-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0280-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p>The other copies, except those addressed to Palfrey, add here the words and hold them as Hostages for the Security of those towns now threatned with destruction.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-02-02-0280-fn-0005-ptr" id="GEWN-03-02-02-0280-fn-0005">5</a>

   <p>This paragraph is omitted in the other copies, except the ones addressed to Palfrey.</p>

</div>
